WEBVTT

02:15.094 --> 02:18.640
<i>You were as blind to Him
as your footprints in the ashes,</i>

02:18.723 --> 02:20.058
<i>but He saw you.</i>

02:22.477 --> 02:24.813
He saw you in those dark corners.

02:26.397 --> 02:30.360
He heard you... My brothers.
He heard those thoughts.

02:32.570 --> 02:34.239
Amen!

02:36.032 --> 02:37.325
Yes. Glory.

02:37.575 --> 02:40.870
You are a stranger to yourself,
and yet He knows you.

02:40.954 --> 02:42.747
- Amen.
- Yes. He does, sir.

02:42.831 --> 02:45.583
And when your hard heart
made you like unto the stone

02:45.667 --> 02:47.669
and broke you from His body,

02:49.087 --> 02:52.006
which is the stars,
and the wind between the stars,

02:52.090 --> 02:53.466
He knew you!

02:55.385 --> 02:57.011
He knew you, again and forever.

02:59.639 --> 03:02.475
This world is a veil.

03:07.897 --> 03:10.900
And the face you wear is not your own.

03:11.526 --> 03:15.989
<i>Parish FD said the church
burned down four months earlier.</i>

03:16.447 --> 03:17.532
<i>No prints.</i>

03:18.116 --> 03:20.910
Put out an APB on Friends of Christ.

03:21.953 --> 03:25.290
A week later, they were in Franklin.

03:28.293 --> 03:29.460
Revival Ministry.

03:30.211 --> 03:31.796
Old-time religion.

03:32.839 --> 03:35.967
You can imagine what
Mr. Charisma thought of that.

03:36.092 --> 03:37.719
<i>It is merely the limitation of your senses.</i>

03:37.802 --> 03:41.014
What do you think the average IQ
of this group is, huh?

03:43.224 --> 03:46.185
Can you see Texas up there
on your high horse?

03:46.269 --> 03:48.271
What do you know about these people?

03:49.564 --> 03:51.608
Just observation and deduction.

03:52.066 --> 03:56.321
I see a propensity for obesity, poverty,
a yen for fairy tales.

03:57.322 --> 03:59.282
Folks putting what few bucks they do have

03:59.365 --> 04:02.118
into little wicker baskets
being passed around.

04:02.201 --> 04:03.244
I think it's safe to say

04:03.328 --> 04:06.164
that nobody here's gonna be
splitting the atom, Marty.

04:06.497 --> 04:07.540
You see that?

04:07.832 --> 04:09.667
Your fucking attitude.

04:10.376 --> 04:13.004
Not everybody wants
to sit alone in an empty room

04:13.087 --> 04:15.089
beating off to murder manuals.

04:15.715 --> 04:19.802
Some folks enjoy community,
a common good.

04:20.345 --> 04:23.431
Yeah, but if the common good's
got to make up fairy tales,

04:23.514 --> 04:25.516
then it's not good for anybody.

04:26.351 --> 04:28.853
Your sorrows pin you to this place.

04:29.562 --> 04:32.315
They divide you from what your heart knows.

04:32.398 --> 04:34.108
And there are a lot of good hearts out there.
I'm looking out there.

04:34.192 --> 04:35.526
I'm seeing a lot of good hearts out there.

04:37.195 --> 04:38.780
I see a lot of joy out there.

04:39.030 --> 04:42.951
I mean, can you imagine
if people didn't believe?

04:43.034 --> 04:44.702
What things they'd get up to?

04:45.411 --> 04:48.873
The exact same thing they do now,
just out in the open.

04:49.540 --> 04:51.542
Bullshit.

04:53.044 --> 04:56.965
It'd be a fucking freak show
of murder and debauchery, and you know it.

04:57.048 --> 04:59.133
If the only thing keeping a person decent

04:59.217 --> 05:01.302
is the expectation of divine reward,

05:01.386 --> 05:03.805
then, brother, that person is a piece of shit.

05:04.681 --> 05:08.101
And I'd like to get as many of them
out in the open as possible.

05:08.393 --> 05:12.271
I guess your judgment
is infallible, piece-of-shit-wise.

05:15.316 --> 05:18.152
You think that notebook is a stone tablet?

05:21.322 --> 05:23.866
What's it say about life?

05:25.994 --> 05:28.079
You got to get together,

05:28.413 --> 05:29.831
tell yourselves stories

05:29.914 --> 05:32.625
that violate every law of the universe,

05:33.126 --> 05:35.420
just to get through the goddamn day? No.

05:36.713 --> 05:39.090
What's that say about your reality, Marty?

05:39.257 --> 05:43.678
When you get to talking like this,
you sound panicked.

05:45.096 --> 05:47.890
<i>You figure it's all a scam, huh?
All them folks.</i>

05:48.516 --> 05:50.435
They're just wrong?

05:51.310 --> 05:53.730
Yeah. Been that way since

05:54.522 --> 05:57.275
one monkey looked at the sun
and told the other monkey,

05:57.358 --> 06:01.195
"He said for you to give me
your fucking share."

06:01.612 --> 06:05.950
People are so goddamn frail,

06:06.034 --> 06:10.288
they'd rather put a coin in a wishing well
than buy dinner.

06:10.455 --> 06:14.792
Jesus Christ, Jesus Christ!
Your arms opened and close.

06:15.084 --> 06:18.546
The echoes of my life could never contain
a single truth about you!

06:18.629 --> 06:20.048
You move the feather in the ash.

06:20.131 --> 06:22.425
You touch the leaf with its flame.

06:23.217 --> 06:27.555
Transference of fear and self-loathing
to an authoritarian vessel.

06:28.347 --> 06:29.557
It's catharsis.

06:30.183 --> 06:32.477
He absorbs their dread with his narrative.

06:32.560 --> 06:34.896
Because of this, he's effective

06:34.979 --> 06:38.274
in proportion to the amount of certainty
he can project.

06:40.526 --> 06:45.031
Certain linguistic anthropologists think
that religion is a language virus

06:45.615 --> 06:48.326
that rewrites pathways in the brain,

06:48.659 --> 06:50.411
dulls critical thinking.

06:50.495 --> 06:54.916
Well, I don't use $10 words as much as you,

06:56.000 --> 06:58.753
but for a guy who sees no point in existence,

06:58.836 --> 07:01.589
you sure fret about it an awful lot.

07:02.507 --> 07:04.675
And you still sound panicked.

07:07.220 --> 07:10.348
At least I'm not racing to a red light.

07:15.269 --> 07:18.314
<i>See, we all got what I call a life trap.</i>

07:19.565 --> 07:22.485
A gene-deep certainty
that things will be different.

07:23.361 --> 07:26.697
That you'll move to another city
and meet the people

07:26.781 --> 07:28.533
that'll be the friends for the rest of your life,

07:28.616 --> 07:31.619
that you'll fall in love and be fulfilled.

07:31.702 --> 07:33.538
Fucking fulfillment.

07:35.206 --> 07:36.582
And closure.

07:36.916 --> 07:38.918
Whatever the fuck those two...

07:39.001 --> 07:42.463
Fucking need empty jars
to hold this shit storm.

07:42.547 --> 07:45.007
Nothing's ever fulfilled.

07:46.134 --> 07:48.261
Not until the very end.

07:48.386 --> 07:49.554
And closure.

07:50.054 --> 07:53.933
No. No, no. Nothing is ever over.

08:02.608 --> 08:06.237
<i>Minister Theriot,
do you recognize this girl?</i>

08:06.904 --> 08:08.281
I don't know for sure.

08:08.364 --> 08:10.241
- Wonderful service.
- Thank you for coming.

08:10.324 --> 08:11.826
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

08:12.076 --> 08:14.370
I want to say it's...

08:15.621 --> 08:16.622
Thank you.

08:17.123 --> 08:18.541
I don't remember the name.

08:18.624 --> 08:20.918
Came pretty regularly
when we was in Eunice.

08:21.794 --> 08:24.505
I can't be sure. We get around since then.

08:24.589 --> 08:26.632
You? Hello.

08:26.799 --> 08:29.010
No, you're right. We saw her in Eunice.

08:29.594 --> 08:31.179
Tina might know her.

08:32.221 --> 08:33.764
How long were you in Eunice?

08:35.266 --> 08:36.517
About six months.

08:36.601 --> 08:38.519
Widow in Opelousas leased us cheap.

08:38.603 --> 08:39.896
We left when it caught fire.

08:39.979 --> 08:41.522
Any idea how that happened?

08:42.773 --> 08:44.775
Your people said "criminal mischief."

08:45.484 --> 08:46.652
If I was to lay odds,

08:46.736 --> 08:49.530
maybe one of the widow's sons
wanted us off the land.

08:49.614 --> 08:52.283
But we move on.
We seek no title. No retribution.

08:52.825 --> 08:54.285
- I'm gonna go find Tina.
- Okay.

08:54.368 --> 08:56.704
Yeah. Great preaching.

08:56.913 --> 08:58.664
How long you been doing this?

08:59.290 --> 09:01.459
Been a preacher almost 20 years.

09:01.751 --> 09:04.128
We've had the Friends of Christ
for the last eight.

09:04.337 --> 09:06.047
You with the church before that?

09:06.589 --> 09:08.299
Independent evangelical.

09:09.050 --> 09:10.509
I came up under Billy Lee Tuttle,

09:10.593 --> 09:13.304
went to his college
in Baton Rouge a couple years.

09:13.971 --> 09:15.139
So back in Eunice,

09:16.015 --> 09:18.226
who painted the mural
on the church wall?

09:18.309 --> 09:20.603
Children from our congregation painted it.

09:22.980 --> 09:24.315
I'm sorry.

09:25.233 --> 09:28.027
Something happen
to this girl you're looking for?

09:28.110 --> 09:31.948
Mr. Theriot, can we see the identification
of your staff members?

09:33.532 --> 09:35.618
<i>You ever see her with anybody?</i>

09:36.160 --> 09:39.038
Wasn't she with someone
the one day? You remember?

09:40.164 --> 09:41.749
The tall man?

09:42.208 --> 09:45.586
Yeah, but I don't know
if she was with him, with him.

09:46.796 --> 09:48.673
Well, can you describe him?

09:51.676 --> 09:55.179
I just saw them talking.
I didn't get close or anything.

09:55.388 --> 09:58.724
He was hunched forward, talking to her.

10:00.017 --> 10:02.353
Kind of a strange face, I think.

10:03.437 --> 10:05.398
Skin shiny around his jaw.

10:06.524 --> 10:08.401
What, like burned?

10:13.364 --> 10:15.366
So did she leave with him?

10:15.783 --> 10:17.868
Yeah. Maybe like that.

10:18.369 --> 10:20.955
<i>Arrested 10-8-89 on a 314.</i>

10:21.038 --> 10:23.916
<i>Spent his last year in solitary
after a gang altercation.</i>

10:24.000 --> 10:26.294
- Print and hold. Thank you.
<i>- Copy that.</i>

10:46.564 --> 10:47.940
Everything check out?

10:48.065 --> 10:49.233
For the most part.

10:51.861 --> 10:54.530
Burt, you spent two years in Angola.

10:54.613 --> 10:57.366
Indecency, public exposure.

10:58.242 --> 11:00.786
Whacking off outside a school.

11:02.413 --> 11:05.249
They gave me bad medicine. I didn't know.

11:05.416 --> 11:07.335
I paid for that.

11:08.127 --> 11:09.420
I paid for that.

11:11.464 --> 11:15.426
Can you account for his whereabouts
December 25th through January 3rd?

11:16.218 --> 11:18.804
Yeah, Christmas to New Year's,
we was in New Roads.

11:18.888 --> 11:21.849
It shouldn't be a problem to find people
who'll vouch for Burt's whereabouts.

11:22.475 --> 11:23.809
We had a good turnout there.

11:23.893 --> 11:25.144
Good turnout.

11:26.145 --> 11:30.274
Detective, what is it you think happened?

11:31.108 --> 11:33.319
Someone killed this girl,
made a big show of it.

11:36.280 --> 11:40.326
Left a painting of the crime scene
on one of your old churches.

11:42.411 --> 11:45.915
"I am the resurrection and the life
for those who believe in me."

11:51.295 --> 11:53.297
Was she raped, Detective?

11:56.008 --> 11:57.927
Why would you ask that?

12:03.099 --> 12:05.309
If you speak to Burt alone,

12:07.019 --> 12:11.023
I believe you'll be adequately convinced
of his innocence, Detective.

12:12.149 --> 12:13.609
Okay, let's do that.

12:14.985 --> 12:18.114
Burt, go with the detective.

12:19.657 --> 12:24.370
<i>The ontological fallacy of expecting
a light at the end of the tunnel,</i>

12:24.495 --> 12:26.831
well, that's what the preacher sells.

12:27.331 --> 12:28.749
Same as a shrink.

12:29.834 --> 12:34.588
See, the preacher, he encourages
your capacity for illusion.

12:34.672 --> 12:37.007
Then he tells you it's a fucking virtue.

12:37.675 --> 12:40.177
Always a buck to be had doing that.

12:41.345 --> 12:45.891
And it's such a desperate sense
of entitlement, isn't it?

12:47.768 --> 12:49.979
"Surely this is all for me.

12:52.106 --> 12:53.190
"Me.

12:54.692 --> 12:56.777
"Me, me... I...

12:57.278 --> 12:59.280
"I'm so fucking important.

12:59.697 --> 13:01.740
"I'm so fucking important." Right?

13:03.284 --> 13:05.619
- Fuck you.
- Excuse us for a second.

13:20.009 --> 13:21.218
<i>I said no!</i>

13:21.302 --> 13:23.471
<i>Easy. I'm not gonna hurt you.</i>

13:23.554 --> 13:25.556
I'm not gonna hurt you.

13:35.399 --> 13:37.693
Compassion is ethics, Detective.

13:38.736 --> 13:40.738
Yes. It is.

13:43.282 --> 13:44.742
<i>I ran checks on all of them.</i>

13:44.825 --> 13:47.578
<i>Everyone's got a clean record except for Burt.</i>

13:47.661 --> 13:51.081
Yeah, I could see this
being some kind of retard job.

13:51.707 --> 13:54.460
He pays for it. Gets ashamed.

13:55.544 --> 13:56.962
Overreacts.

13:57.963 --> 14:01.634
Tries to redeem the act, you know?

14:02.801 --> 14:04.428
That's not bad, Marty.

14:05.429 --> 14:08.140
Yeah, I got all the way there
without your help.

14:08.307 --> 14:09.934
But it's not him.

14:11.685 --> 14:14.355
He did a deuce at the Farm for dick wagging.

14:14.438 --> 14:16.857
Should've been in a mental ward
to begin with.

14:17.274 --> 14:19.276
- Give me the second half.
- Angola.

14:20.069 --> 14:22.112
Some Bloods caught him in the shower.

14:22.613 --> 14:24.698
Took his balls off with a razor.

14:24.907 --> 14:26.116
They were sloppy about it.

14:26.492 --> 14:27.952
Oh, Jesus!

14:31.121 --> 14:32.206
Still...

14:32.706 --> 14:33.916
I braced him.

14:35.000 --> 14:37.211
He shit himself. Literally.

14:42.424 --> 14:45.970
We can put some troopers on this place,
have them surveil it,

14:46.804 --> 14:48.556
but I think we should move on.

14:48.806 --> 14:49.974
The tall man.

14:50.683 --> 14:52.476
Well, that could be bullshit.

14:53.102 --> 14:55.229
One threw it out
and the other one picked up on it.

14:55.312 --> 14:56.814
No, Burt knew.

14:57.648 --> 14:59.358
He saw the tall man, too.

15:00.484 --> 15:03.529
This. That Marie Fontenot thing.

15:03.612 --> 15:05.322
There's no way Lange was his first.

15:05.406 --> 15:07.032
No fucking way.

15:11.745 --> 15:14.373
Rosie,
can you help them get out, please?

15:27.303 --> 15:29.179
<i>We haven't matched any signatures.</i>

15:30.472 --> 15:35.019
One guy in the Fed database used crowns,
another, a set of antlers.

15:35.603 --> 15:37.021
Michigan lifer.

15:37.730 --> 15:39.898
Then we called the signature wrong.

15:42.484 --> 15:45.613
We don't know if there's any connection
to Marie Fontenot.

15:47.615 --> 15:50.868
Yeah, but the lattices, the symbology.

15:52.202 --> 15:54.371
There's some kind of culture to it, Marty.

15:57.875 --> 16:01.295
He wanted us to find this one,
like he was showing off.

16:02.212 --> 16:04.173
The cane fields are his stage.

16:06.300 --> 16:07.968
Make a suggestion, then.

16:08.052 --> 16:12.264
We could start at zero,
they're going to hand it to the task force.

16:13.182 --> 16:14.642
Well, somebody missed something.

16:14.975 --> 16:16.977
We need to go back, check all files.

16:17.061 --> 16:20.230
Any DBs in state the last five years,
we start there.

16:21.774 --> 16:23.233
We don't have the hours.

16:24.610 --> 16:26.070
Shit, man. Look...

16:27.154 --> 16:29.365
I've noticed you have
a tendency toward myopia.

16:29.907 --> 16:32.660
Tunnel vision. Blows investigations.

16:32.951 --> 16:35.746
Vision skews, twists evidence.

16:37.790 --> 16:39.249
You're obsessive.

16:40.334 --> 16:43.337
You're obsessive, too. Just not about the job.

16:44.797 --> 16:46.006
Not me, brother.

16:46.757 --> 16:49.760
I keep things even. Separate.

16:50.511 --> 16:53.597
Like the way I can have this one beer
without needing 20.

16:53.681 --> 16:57.017
People incapable of guilt
usually do have a good time.

17:02.398 --> 17:04.733
I try not to be too hard on myself.

17:06.235 --> 17:07.695
Well, that's real big of you.

17:08.445 --> 17:10.698
You know the real difference
between you and me?

17:10.781 --> 17:11.782
Yeah.

17:12.116 --> 17:13.117
Denial.

17:14.576 --> 17:17.329
The difference is that I know the difference

17:17.413 --> 17:19.415
between an idea and a fact.

17:19.498 --> 17:23.377
You are incapable of admitting doubt.

17:23.460 --> 17:25.379
Now that sounds like denial to me.

17:27.256 --> 17:28.590
I doubt that.

17:33.470 --> 17:37.474
We'll put out an APB
on any tall man with facial scarring.

17:38.058 --> 17:39.309
Okay.

17:39.476 --> 17:42.563
Telex the hospitals for patients that fit.

17:42.646 --> 17:43.814
Good.

17:58.495 --> 18:01.165
<i>So Cohle was trying
to keep it from the task force.</i>

18:02.374 --> 18:03.625
Looking back,

18:04.460 --> 18:06.003
you ever think maybe

18:06.336 --> 18:09.131
he tried to push things
where he wanted them to go?

18:11.175 --> 18:15.012
No. We went where the case led us.

18:15.721 --> 18:17.181
But you took it up, though?

18:17.431 --> 18:18.724
His serial theory?

18:19.516 --> 18:22.853
Well, as arrogant as he could be, he was right.

18:23.061 --> 18:26.148
I mean, that's how we got our man.

18:29.777 --> 18:31.445
but I like it this way.

18:31.862 --> 18:33.280
It's steady.

18:33.363 --> 18:34.865
Bullshit. Really.

18:34.948 --> 18:37.826
Look, I did all the counseling and stuff,
you know.

18:37.910 --> 18:40.454
This is just the way things are.

18:40.537 --> 18:42.206
No, things don't stay the same.

18:42.289 --> 18:44.792
Pick up what you keep
and you leave the rest behind.

18:44.875 --> 18:46.168
People get better.

18:46.335 --> 18:47.419
That's the thing.

18:48.128 --> 18:49.588
I think I am better.

18:50.380 --> 18:52.966
- You really think so?
- Trust me.

18:54.259 --> 18:57.429
Maybe you just think you prefer it this way
'cause it's what you're used to.

18:58.055 --> 18:59.765
Your life accommodates you.

19:00.599 --> 19:02.684
You don't have to be afraid of loss.

19:05.229 --> 19:07.231
Those other guys I was telling you about,

19:07.314 --> 19:10.734
they get a dog, a fish, what have you.

19:10.818 --> 19:13.070
You start with that, you live with it.

19:32.506 --> 19:35.092
Hell, I suppose you could
set me up with a nurse.

19:36.051 --> 19:37.970
Give me some of the good drugs.

19:39.847 --> 19:41.098
Would be a start.

19:43.517 --> 19:45.060
- Daddy!
- Hey, kids.

19:45.853 --> 19:46.937
Hey, honey.

19:47.229 --> 19:48.480
Hi, there, Marty.

19:54.820 --> 19:57.155
- What's going on, Rust?
- Brought the mower back.

19:59.157 --> 20:02.911
- You mowed my yard?
- Yeah, I saw it needed mowing.

20:02.995 --> 20:05.372
Return the favor. Borrowing.

20:05.789 --> 20:07.249
We got йtouffйe.

20:07.791 --> 20:10.127
Trying to get Rust to stay for dinner.

20:10.752 --> 20:13.964
Oh, yeah? Stay for dinner, Rust.

20:15.716 --> 20:17.885
No, I think I got to get.

20:19.553 --> 20:21.388
Maggie, thank you for the tea.

20:22.639 --> 20:24.349
I'm sorry to hear that.

20:26.018 --> 20:27.477
See you Monday.

20:28.812 --> 20:30.314
I'll walk you out.

20:32.482 --> 20:33.483
Hey!

20:34.651 --> 20:35.777
Hey!

20:39.323 --> 20:40.324
What?

20:41.241 --> 20:46.079
What the hell do you think you're doing, man,
at my house when I'm not here?

20:47.664 --> 20:49.166
Returning the mower.

20:49.249 --> 20:50.584
You know what I mean.

20:51.168 --> 20:54.171
You mow my lawn?

20:55.339 --> 20:58.383
Just what do you think I'd be doing over here
when you're not around, Marty?

20:59.217 --> 21:01.345
What's our problem?

21:01.803 --> 21:03.180
You and me.

21:03.263 --> 21:04.514
No problem.

21:04.848 --> 21:07.976
I just don't ever want you mowing my lawn.
All right?

21:08.060 --> 21:10.896
I like mowing my lawn.

21:44.513 --> 21:45.681
That's your team, Daddy?

21:45.764 --> 21:48.600
Yeah, baby. We want them to win.

22:01.363 --> 22:04.032
Hey, Audrey,

22:04.533 --> 22:09.413
your mom and I want to talk to you a minute
about those drawings you did in school.

22:09.913 --> 22:10.914
Yeah?

22:11.289 --> 22:13.417
- Mace, run to your room.
- Why?

22:13.667 --> 22:16.044
Because I said so. Run to... Go.

22:17.045 --> 22:18.046
Go on.

22:19.756 --> 22:20.757
Go.

22:24.511 --> 22:25.929
Go. Run.

22:31.476 --> 22:32.644
