45:33.774 --> 45:35.859
- What break?
- KA of the victim.

45:35.943 --> 45:38.237
Might've known the killer, boss.
Might've seen him.

45:38.320 --> 45:41.532
We follow up. We still got a few days.

45:42.825 --> 45:45.160
Two days, then it goes to task force.

45:45.244 --> 45:46.453
You two catch again.

45:48.956 --> 45:53.419
You try that serial theory on him,
he will pull you just for spite.

45:53.502 --> 45:55.421
Pelican Island's two hours away.

46:03.846 --> 46:05.180
<i>What church teaches that?</i>

46:05.264 --> 46:07.307
<i>The Christian Church does not teach that.</i>

46:07.391 --> 46:09.268
<i>The Catholic Church does not...</i>

46:16.733 --> 46:17.776
Hey.

46:19.403 --> 46:24.283
You think a man can love
two women at once?

46:25.117 --> 46:28.454
I mean, be in love with them?

46:29.037 --> 46:31.248
I don't think that man can love.

46:32.416 --> 46:34.376
At least not the way that he means.

46:35.544 --> 46:38.714
The inadequacies of reality always set in.

46:41.049 --> 46:44.428
This pipeline's carved up
this coast like a jigsaw.

46:44.511 --> 46:47.389
The place is gonna be underwater in 30 years.

46:50.893 --> 46:54.229
Do you think...

46:54.313 --> 46:55.772
Do you wonder ever

46:57.774 --> 46:59.651
if you're a bad man?

47:00.360 --> 47:02.362
No, I don't wonder, Marty.

47:04.156 --> 47:06.074
The world needs bad men.

47:09.912 --> 47:12.998
We keep the other bad men from the door.

47:49.952 --> 47:51.328
That's him.

47:55.832 --> 47:58.794
<i>When was the last time
you saw your granddaughter?</i>

48:00.003 --> 48:01.964
She left four years ago.

48:02.047 --> 48:03.423
Like her ma.

48:04.007 --> 48:06.134
I wasn't surprised they found her like that.

48:06.802 --> 48:09.888
Everybody think they're gonna be
something they're not.

48:09.972 --> 48:13.517
Everybody think they got these big plans.

48:13.934 --> 48:17.437
She had a boyfriend you know about? A man?

48:17.938 --> 48:20.732
She took up with that Ledoux fellow.

48:20.816 --> 48:21.817
Older boy.

48:21.900 --> 48:23.068
Shit family.

48:23.610 --> 48:24.987
Run off with him.

48:26.113 --> 48:29.032
I ain't never had nobody ask me
about him before.

48:29.283 --> 48:32.286
They just tell me she died in the flood.

48:32.661 --> 48:35.163
That Ledoux family,
they still live around here?

48:35.539 --> 48:37.457
Maybe a cousin or two.

48:38.333 --> 48:39.710
Been shrinking every year.

48:40.085 --> 48:43.338
Hurricane Andrew wiped most
of the folks out around here.

48:44.381 --> 48:47.259
So you got a full name on that Ledoux boy?

48:48.802 --> 48:50.012
Reggie.

48:50.637 --> 48:51.972
Reggie Ledoux.

48:52.764 --> 48:54.933
Father's Bart Ledoux.

48:55.017 --> 48:57.686
Works offshore. Drunkard.

48:57.978 --> 48:59.855
I heard he died.

49:00.689 --> 49:02.357
So, where'd Rianne go to school?

49:02.441 --> 49:04.943
Light of Way, when it was open.

49:05.277 --> 49:08.196
Kids either went there
or they were bused to Abbeville.

49:08.280 --> 49:11.950
State said a kid got to be bused
two hours away to school.

49:12.701 --> 49:15.162
I ain't too big on them God-botherers.

49:15.704 --> 49:17.205
Between them and the government.

49:18.040 --> 49:20.542
How about her parents? Other relatives?

49:21.627 --> 49:23.545
Father's a merchant seaman.

49:24.046 --> 49:26.298
Mother's in California, last I heard.

49:26.381 --> 49:29.176
Do you have anything of hers?

49:29.259 --> 49:34.723
Possessions, anything that'd give us
an idea of what she might've been like?

49:36.516 --> 49:38.518
What you boys looking all this up for?

49:39.353 --> 49:41.563
I was told she drowned in the flood.

49:42.564 --> 49:44.149
Now, I ain't no idiot.

49:44.232 --> 49:46.777
You telling me she ain't done drown?

49:47.277 --> 49:48.487
We don't know that, sir.

49:48.570 --> 49:51.198
We're just looking for a man
that might've known her.

49:51.948 --> 49:52.991
Who?

49:53.700 --> 49:55.744
That's what we're trying to figure out.

49:56.745 --> 49:59.665
<i>He ended up having a little box of her stuff,</i>

49:59.748 --> 50:02.209
had her last yearbook, 10th grade.

50:03.669 --> 50:05.754
Not a hint of feeling from the old man.

50:06.922 --> 50:08.048
Kind of guy...

50:08.548 --> 50:09.549
Blinders.

50:10.926 --> 50:13.595
But why'd he keep the box, huh?

50:14.262 --> 50:15.722
Did he ask himself?

50:18.433 --> 50:21.311
Anyway, I guess that's one way to do it.

50:21.395 --> 50:23.772
Keep your eyes on the crab traps.

50:25.440 --> 50:27.943
He kind of reminded me of Rust a little bit.

50:32.948 --> 50:34.449
This school is small.

50:35.659 --> 50:37.077
Grades 1 through 12.

50:39.830 --> 50:41.957
Rianne Olivier, here she is.

50:43.250 --> 50:44.793
Tenth grade.

50:51.925 --> 50:55.053
This school was part of Tuttle's foundation.

51:15.991 --> 51:17.242
Good afternoon.

51:17.325 --> 51:18.910
Afternoon.

51:18.994 --> 51:21.121
This place shut down in '92, right?

51:22.080 --> 51:24.750
- Yeah, way I heard it.
- What'd you hear?

51:24.833 --> 51:27.002
Well, Andrew blew it out.

51:27.669 --> 51:31.089
Guess they didn't think
it was worth cleaning up.

51:32.382 --> 51:33.592
Do you work here, then?

51:34.426 --> 51:36.303
No, sir. I work for the parish.

51:36.386 --> 51:37.846
Cover several properties.

51:39.347 --> 51:40.682
<i>I-23?</i>

51:44.186 --> 51:45.604
I-23, go.

51:45.687 --> 51:47.689
<i>I got comeback on your R and I.</i>

51:47.773 --> 51:51.693
<i>Reginald Ledoux. DOB 11-13-60.</i>

51:52.027 --> 51:55.864
You know anybody who went here
or worked here back then?

51:57.949 --> 51:58.950
No, sir.

51:59.034 --> 52:01.369
I only been coming here the last few months.

52:01.828 --> 52:03.872
Parish added it to my work order.

52:12.422 --> 52:13.840
Thank you for your time.

52:18.094 --> 52:20.180
Who walks that fucking slow?

52:23.058 --> 52:24.392
What do you got?

52:24.935 --> 52:26.603
R and I just came back.

52:26.686 --> 52:29.147
Reggie Ledoux skipped parole
eight months ago.

52:29.856 --> 52:32.317
He's got a statch rape complaint.
Charges dropped.

52:32.400 --> 52:38.907
But '93, he's busted in connection to
a narcotics lab used to make meth and LSD,

52:38.990 --> 52:41.493
which Dora Lange and Rianne were full of.

52:41.576 --> 52:42.744
Right.

52:43.078 --> 52:44.871
Ledoux did two years at Avoyelles,

52:44.955 --> 52:47.999
and guess who his cellmate was
the last four months?

52:48.083 --> 52:49.543
Charlie Lange.

52:50.168 --> 52:51.795
I gotta give you this one.

52:53.839 --> 52:56.716
<i>I started to believe you were
going a little off your nut.</i>

52:56.800 --> 52:59.511
I mean, you're bonkers, just not on this.

52:59.594 --> 53:01.304
All right. Well, where's Ledoux?

53:01.388 --> 53:03.682
Getting a list of relatives, KAs.

53:03.765 --> 53:06.059
Been out of pocket since jumping parole.

53:06.142 --> 53:07.352
We'll find him.

53:07.435 --> 53:08.436
This makes sense.

53:08.520 --> 53:09.688
It looks good, baby.

53:09.771 --> 53:11.273
All right. We are on our way.

53:11.356 --> 53:13.275
- To Avoyelles.
- Fuck, yeah, Martin. Let's go.

53:13.441 --> 53:17.195
I'm calling the interstate APB
and the U.S. Marshals on this.

53:17.362 --> 53:18.947
I-23, dispatch.

53:19.197 --> 53:20.365
<i>Come in, I-23.</i>

53:20.448 --> 53:21.575
What can I say?

53:21.658 --> 53:24.369
I thought for a minute you just liked looking
at pictures of dead people.

53:24.452 --> 53:27.205
I need an all-state APB
on one Reginald Ledoux.

53:27.289 --> 53:28.874
R and I came back with info.

53:28.957 --> 53:31.293
All U.S. Marshals
and highway patrol, be advised.

53:31.376 --> 53:32.836
Detain on sight. Over.

53:32.919 --> 53:35.297
<i>Roger that, Detective. We'll process that now.</i>

53:39.467 --> 53:45.640
And finally, we arrive at Reginald Ledoux.

53:50.979 --> 53:51.938
<i>Come on, man.</i>

53:52.022 --> 53:54.900
You wanna ask me, ask, God damn it.

53:55.817 --> 53:57.569
You ever been in a gun fight?

53:59.070 --> 54:00.071
No.

54:01.573 --> 54:04.326
Well, then how the fuck you gonna know
what I'm talking about?

54:07.162 --> 54:08.997
<i>Man, that place...</i>

54:10.165 --> 54:11.625
<i>I never...</i>

54:12.876 --> 54:16.171
<i>It reminded me of my pop talking about 'Nam.</i>

54:17.672 --> 54:19.132
<i>And the jungle thing.</i>

54:21.217 --> 54:24.346
Look, me talking about
what happened back then,

54:24.763 --> 54:27.015
that ain't gonna do you any good now.

54:30.435 --> 54:31.811
This.

54:33.521 --> 54:35.398
This is what I'm talking about.

54:37.359 --> 54:40.612
This is what I mean
when I'm talking about time

54:41.321 --> 54:44.032
and death, and futility.

54:45.867 --> 54:47.953
There are broader ideas at work.

54:48.036 --> 54:52.916
Mainly, what is owed between us,
as a society, for our mutual illusions.

54:52.999 --> 54:56.878
Fourteen straight hours of staring at DBs,

54:56.962 --> 54:59.589
these are the things you think of.

55:00.757 --> 55:02.050
You ever done that?

55:04.844 --> 55:08.807
<i>You look in their eyes, even in a picture.</i>

55:08.890 --> 55:11.893
<i>Doesn't matter if they're dead or alive,
you can still read them.</i>

55:12.852 --> 55:14.270
<i>And you know what you see?</i>

55:16.731 --> 55:18.191
They welcomed it.

55:22.070 --> 55:28.368
Not at first, but right there in the last instant,
it's an unmistakable relief.

55:28.618 --> 55:33.248
See, 'cause they were afraid
and now they saw for the very first time

55:33.915 --> 55:37.085
<i>how easy it was to just let go.</i>

55:38.169 --> 55:41.673
<i>And they saw...
In that last nanosecond, they saw</i>

55:42.757 --> 55:44.426
<i>what they were.</i>

55:44.884 --> 55:47.679
<i>That you, yourself, this whole, big drama,</i>

55:47.762 --> 55:52.392
<i>it was never anything
but a jerry-rig of presumption and dumb will.</i>

55:53.184 --> 55:54.769
<i>And you could just let go.</i>

55:55.437 --> 55:58.273
<i>Finally know that you
didn't have to hold on so tight.</i>

56:00.442 --> 56:02.027
To realize that

56:03.403 --> 56:04.779
in all your life,

56:05.280 --> 56:08.366
all your love, all your hate,
all your memory, all your pain,

56:08.450 --> 56:10.076
it was all the same thing.

56:10.827 --> 56:12.454
It was all the same dream,

56:12.537 --> 56:15.457
a dream that you had inside a locked room.

56:18.043 --> 56:22.839
A dream about being a person.

56:31.014 --> 56:32.682
<i>And like a lot of dreams,</i>

56:38.980 --> 56:41.107
there's a monster at the end of it.
